# Orchestration (Everything Claude Code → Cursor)

Sourced and adapted from [affaan-m/everything-claude-code](https://github.com/affaan-m/everything-claude-code) (`.cursor/rules`), for use in **Cursor** on FlexiQueue.

## Precedence

When anything here conflicts with **`agentic-workflow.mdc`**, **`plan-first-and-bead-scope.mdc`**, or **`stack-conventions.mdc`**, the **FlexiQueue** rules win (beads, phase contracts, Laravel + Inertia + Svelte stack).

## Roles in Cursor (no `~/.claude/agents/`)

Claude Code “agents” are **prompted subagents**. In Cursor, approximate them by:

- **Planner** — Break work into steps, name risks and dependencies, align with `docs/architecture/` and the current bead.
- **Architect** — Boundaries, services vs controllers, data flow, security boundaries.
- **TDD** — Failing test first, then minimal implementation (see `ecc-testing.mdc` and project PHPUnit cadence).
- **Code reviewer** — After substantive edits: correctness, edge cases, consistency with existing patterns.
- **Security reviewer** — Before merge-sensitive changes: authz, secrets, injection, CSRF (see `ecc-security.mdc`).

Use the **Task / explore** tool for independent searches in parallel when it reduces wall-clock time.

## Parallel execution

For **independent** investigations (e.g. “find all usages”, “read three unrelated files”, “grep two patterns”), run them **in parallel** instead of strictly serial steps.

## Multi-perspective pass (optional, heavy tasks)

For risky or cross-cutting changes, explicitly consider: correctness, security, consistency with project conventions, and unnecessary duplication.
